Biograpy

Jackie Groenen is a Dutch professional footballer born on December 17, 1994. Known for her exceptional skills and versatility, she has made a significant impact in the world of women's football. Starting her career at the youth academy of sc Heerenveen, Groenen quickly rose through the ranks and went on to play for top clubs such as FFC Frankfurt and Manchester United. Her prowess as a midfielder, with exceptional ball control and vision, has earned her numerous accolades, including the Silver Ball at the 2019 FIFA Women's World Cup. Off the field, Groenen is admired for her humble and down-to-earth nature, serving as a role model for aspiring athletes. With her dedication and passion for the game, she continues to inspire both fans and fellow players alike, leaving an indelible mark on the beautiful game of football.
